From this project, I realized how important it is to have a GitHub project setup, 
even if you're a solo developer working on a project. I knew very little about GitHub beforehand, 
due to having some assignments on it in the past. However, I only ever learnt the basics of GitHub such as how to post your code online, 
how to access other users codes and projects, and how to assign yourself to a task. However, I never knew what a pull request was, nor what a .mb file is. 
However, starting this project, I learnt a lot aboout GitHub and will now be using it for future projects and assignments. I realized how useful it is to store your code online in this website, publicly or privately. 
I've worked on quiet a few projects before and I realized how messy it got storing all of them. I ended up deleting some of them too as it got too messy. However, now that I know how to use GitHub, I will be starting to use it more often.
It was quiet challenging learning GitHub since at first I wasn't much of a fun learning it. 
